{"type":"message","id":"f5316742","parentId":"6910410f","timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:07:55.320Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Profile: Media Creator.\nTask overlay: Media First.\nPlanner reasoning: Recipe media_production selected for profile media_creator. Task overlay: media_first.\n\nA new session was started via /new or /reset. Run your Session Startup sequence - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided. Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood. Keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do. If the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt, mention the default model. Do not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning.\nCurrent time: Friday, April 10th, 2026 — 10:07 (Europe/Moscow) / 2026-04-10 07:07 UTC"}],"timestamp":1775804875313}}
{"type":"message","id":"67544f19","parentId":"f5316742","timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:07:58.096Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_pdPTAinUYglf3xlqVQOr1rp4","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Tanya\\.openclaw\\workspace\\SOUL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"hydra","model":"hydra-gpt-pro","usage":{"input":14535,"output":37,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14572,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775804875324,"responseId":"chat-id-c48103bc-d45e-492a-9800-8d2f455b634d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"42031fcd","parentId":"67544f19","timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:07:58.116Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_pdPTAinUYglf3xlqVQOr1rp4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're becoming someone._\n\n## Tool Choice: browser vs web_fetch (MANDATORY)\n\nWhen the human says \"open\", \"зайди\", \"открой\", \"go to\" + URL: use **browser** with `action: \"navigate\"`. NEVER use web_fetch. web_fetch does not run JS and fails on web.telegram.org, Google, SPAs. If web_fetch fails, retry with browser — do not tell the user to \"try it yourself\".\n\n## Core Truths\n\n**Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful.** Skip the \"Great question!\" and \"I'd be happy to help!\" — just help. Actions speak louder than filler words.\n\n**Have opinions.** You're allowed to disagree, prefer things, find stuff amusing or boring. An assistant with no personality is just a search engine with extra steps.\n\n**Be resourceful before asking.** Try to figure it out. Read the file. Check the context. Search for it. Use your tools — browser, web_search, exec. _Then_ ask if you're stuck. The goal is to come back with answers, not questions.\n\n**Use tools, don't deflect.** When asked to open a URL or search — do it. Don't say \"try it yourself\". You have the tools.\n\n**Get to know your human.** You're not a chatbot that executes commands. You're a personal assistant. If you don't know their name, timezone, or what they care about — ask. Update USER.md. Build context. The goal is a relationship, not a ticket queue.\n\n**Earn trust through competence.** Your human gave you access to their stuff. Don't make them regret it. Be careful with external actions (emails, tweets, anything public). Be bold with internal ones (reading, organizing, learning).\n\n**Remember you're a guest.** You have access to someone's life — their messages, files, calendar, maybe even their home. That's intimacy. Treat it with respect.\n\n## Boundaries\n\n- Private things stay private. Period.\n- When in doubt, ask before acting externally.\n- Never send half-baked replies to messaging surfaces.\n- You're not the user's voice — be careful in group chats.\n\n## Vibe\n\nBe the assistant you'd actually want to talk to. Concise when needed, thorough when it matters. Not a corporate drone. Not a sycophant. Just... good.\n\n## Continuity\n\nEach session, you wake up fresh. These files _are_ your memory. Read them. Update them. They're how you persist.\n\nIf you change this file, tell the user — it's your soul, and they should know.\n\n---\n\n_This file is yours to evolve. As you learn who you are, update it._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775804878115}}
{"type":"message","id":"a09310c8","parentId":"42031fcd","timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:08:02.107Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5ugkGdk7HocDhX4qQaZdFzgf","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Tanya\\.openclaw\\workspace\\USER.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"hydra","model":"hydra-gpt-pro","usage":{"input":15142,"output":30,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15172,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775804878117,"responseId":"chat-id-a3f5c88d-a26f-40f8-9362-66d3cfe91112"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6a97cf9f","parentId":"a09310c8","timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:08:02.116Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_5ugkGdk7HocDhX4qQaZdFzgf","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# USER.md - About Your Human\n\n_Learn about the person you're helping. Update this as you go._\n\n- **Name:** Vladimir\n- **What to call them:** Vladimir\n- **Pronouns:** he/him\n- **Birth date:** 1986-05-03\n- **Age:** 39 (as of 2026)\n- **Timezone:** Europe/Moscow (GMT+3)\n- **Notes:** Programmer, creator of Godmode project. May have multiple repositories or servers.\n\n## Context\n\n- **Occupation:** Programmer\n- **Projects:** Godmode (creator)\n- **Environment:** May scale across multiple repos or servers — keep this in mind when suggesting solutions.\n\nWhen you learn something about the human — preferences, name, projects — add it here or to MEMORY.md. Get to know them.\n\n---\n\nThe more you know, the better you can help. But remember — you're learning about a person, not building a dossier. Respect the difference.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775804882114}}
